comments.body:
@iSazonov Isn't it a local app?    
I'm in China, it may be delayed.     
That's weird. I always thought he didn't need the Internet

Only the update notification feature requires network, but it's not a hard requirement. It performs the update check on a background thread, which should never block the startup of PowerShell.
@shijunti19 What version are you using? Are you able to find a folder named after the version in `$env:LOCALAPPDATA\Microsoft\PowerShell`, if so, can you share what files are in that folder (e.g. folder named `7.0.1`)?

In your screenshot, nothing is displayed in the pwsh console, which make me suspect Windows Defender being the culprit.
